# ✅ CORRECT ENTERPRISE SOLUTION (Red Hat aligned)

👉 **Use OpenShift user-workload monitoring properly (no custom TLS hacks)**

---

# 🔥 STEP-BY-STEP CLEAN SOLUTION

## ✅ 1. Enable user workload monitoring (CRITICAL)

Ask/OpenShift admin verify:

```bash
oc get configmap cluster-monitoring-config -n openshift-monitoring
```

Must contain:

```yaml
data:
  config.yaml: |
    enableUserWorkload: true
```

---

## ✅ 2. Label your namespace

```bash
oc label namespace dev-kafka openshift.io/user-monitoring=true --overwrite
```

---

## ✅ 3. PodMonitor (your YAML is mostly correct)

Just ensure **THIS is correct**:

```yaml
namespaceSelector:
  matchNames:
    - dev-kafka
```

And port:

```yaml
port: tcp-prometheus
```

---

## ✅ 4. RBAC (you already did 👍)

```bash
oc adm policy add-cluster-role-to-user cluster-monitoring-view \
  -z dev-console-console-serviceaccount \
  -n dev-kafka
```

✔️ This allows console to query Prometheus

---

## ❗ 5. MOST IMPORTANT FIX (you missed this)

👉 **Use INTERNAL THANOS SERVICE (NOT route)**
👉 AND disable TLS expectation

---

## ✅ FINAL CORRECT Console YAML

```yaml
metricsSources:
  - name: kafka-metrics
    type: openshift-monitoring
    url: "http://thanos-querier.openshift-monitoring.svc:9091"
```

---

### 🔴 NO TLS BLOCK

### 🔴 NO CERT SECRET

### 🔴 NO HARDCODED CA

---

## ✅ 6. Kafka cluster mapping

```yaml
kafkaClusters:
  - name: dev-kafka-cluster
    namespace: dev-kafka
    listener: plain
    metricsSource: kafka-metrics
```

---

## ✅ 7. Force reconcile

```bash
oc patch consoles.console.streamshub.github.com dev-console -n dev-kafka \
  -p '{"metadata":{"annotations":{"force-reconcile":"'$(date +%s)'"}}}' \
  --type=merge
```

---

## ✅ 8. Restart

```bash
oc rollout restart deployment/dev-console-console-deployment -n dev-kafka
```

